components.kdoc:
Aurum's primary button component.

Wraps `material3.Button` internally, overriding every visible style
parameter from Aurum tokens. Features consume this composable -- never
`material3.Button` directly.

Three visual [variant] variants ([AurumButtonVariant]) and three [size]
variants ([AurumButtonSize]) are supported. Optional [leading] and
[trailing] slots accept icon composables for icon-and-label buttons.

@param label the button label text
@param onClick called when the button is clicked
@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply
@param variant the visual style variant -- defaults to [AurumButtonVariant.Primary]
@param size the size variant -- defaults to [AurumButtonSize.Medium]
@param isFullWidth whether the button fills its parent width -- defaults to `false`
@param isLoading whether to show a loading spinner in place of the label -- defaults to `false`
@param leading optional composable slot rendered before the label (e.g. an icon)
@param trailing optional composable slot rendered after the label (e.g. an icon)
@param enabled whether the button is interactive -- defaults to `true`

Aurum's icon-only button primitive.

Wraps `material3.IconButton` internally, preserving its 48 dp minimum
touch target. Features consume this composable — never
`material3.IconButton` directly.

The [content] slot typically renders an [AurumIcon]. The caller controls
the icon size and tint via [AurumIcon]'s parameters.

@param onClick called when the button is clicked
@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply
@param enabled whether the button is interactive — defaults to `true`
@param content the composable content — typically an [AurumIcon]

Aurum's link button -- a text-only button with no background or border.

Per the Figma spec, this is a separate component from [AurumButton].
It renders brand-purple text (Inter Bold 14sp) with no fill or outline,
using a 12 dp corner-radius clip for ripple feedback.

Height is fixed at 56 dp (large-size equivalent).

@param label the link label text
@param onClick called when the link is clicked
@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply
@param leading optional composable slot rendered before the label (e.g. an icon)
@param trailing optional composable slot rendered after the label (e.g. an icon)
@param enabled whether the link is interactive -- defaults to `true`

Aurum's divider primitive — a thin horizontal line used to separate
content sections.

This is a **scratch** component — a styled [Box], not `material3.HorizontalDivider`.

@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply
@param color the divider colour — defaults to the surface low-contrast
  border token
@param thickness the divider height — defaults to [Aurum.borderWidth.xs]
  (0.5 dp hairline)

components.signature:
@Composable
fun AurumDivider(
    modifier: Modifier = Modifier,
    color: Color = Aurum.colors.surface.borderSurfaceLowContrast,
    thickness: Dp = Aurum.borderWidth.xs,
)

components.kdoc:
Aurum's circular progress spinner.

A **scratch** component — drawn directly on [Canvas] from
`androidx.compose.foundation`, not derived from any Material 3 indicator.
Replaces the duplicated `CircularProgressLoader` found across 3+ modules.

The spinner draws a full-circle track in [trackColor] and animates a 90-degree
arc segment in [color] rotating at a constant speed.

@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply
@param color the spinning arc colour — defaults to the primary interactive
  background token
@param trackColor the background ring colour — defaults to the mid-contrast
  surface token
@param strokeWidth the thickness of the ring — defaults to [Aurum.borderWidth.lg]
@param size the overall diameter — defaults to [Aurum.iconSize.xxl]

components.signature:
@Composable
fun AurumSkeleton(
    modifier: Modifier = Modifier,
    shape: Shape = Aurum.shape.sm,
)

components.kdoc:
Aurum's OTP (one-time password) input component.

Renders a row of underline-style digit cells that the user fills sequentially.
A single hidden [BasicTextField] captures keyboard input; the visible cells
are decorative columns (digit + coloured underline bar).

This is a **scratch** component — built entirely on
`androidx.compose.foundation` with zero `material3` imports.

@param value the current OTP string (digits only, length <= [length].count)
@param onValueChange callback invoked when the user types or deletes a digit
@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply to the outer column
@param length the number of digit cells — 4 or 6
@param label optional label text displayed above the cells
@param helperText optional helper/error/success text displayed below the cells
@param validationState controls underline and helper text colour
@param enabled whether the input accepts user interaction
@param onComplete optional callback invoked once all digits have been entered

A phone-number-specific text field: country code + divider + digit input.

Delegates to [AurumTextField] with a fixed leading slot that renders an
optional [flag] composable, the [countryCode] text, and a thin vertical
divider. Defaults to a phone keyboard and a 10-digit max length; input
is silently filtered to digits only.

@param value the current phone number (digits only)
@param onValueChange callback invoked when the input changes
@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply
@param countryCode the country-code text shown in the leading slot,
  e.g. `"+91"` — defaults to `"+91"`
@param flag optional composable rendered before [countryCode]; supply a
  country flag image here (nothing is shown when `null`)
@param label optional field label — same semantics as [AurumTextField]
@param placeholder placeholder text — defaults to `"Phone Number"`
@param helperText assistive text below the field
@param errorText error text — when non-null the field shows error styling
@param successText success text — when non-null (and no error) the field
  shows success styling
@param isError whether the field is in error state
@param isSuccess whether the field is in success state
@param enabled whether the field accepts input
@param readOnly whether the field is read-only
@param maxLength max number of digits accepted — defaults to `10`
@param keyboardActions IME action callbacks

A search-specific text field with a leading search icon and an optional
trailing clear button.

Delegates to [AurumTextField] internally, applying a pill shape
([Aurum.shape.pill]) and `singleLine = true` to produce a compact
search-bar appearance.

The clear icon appears only when [value] is not empty **and** [onClear]
is provided.

@param value the current search query
@param onValueChange callback invoked when the query changes
@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply
@param placeholder placeholder text — defaults to "Search"
@param enabled whether the field accepts input
@param onClear optional callback invoked when the clear button is tapped;
  when `null` no clear button is shown

Aurum's primary text-input field.

Wraps [M3OutlinedTextField] and applies Aurum colour, shape, and
typography tokens. All visible style parameters are resolved from
`Aurum.*` tokens — callers never need to pass raw [Color] or style values.

Below the field, an optional helper, error, or success message is displayed
in [Aurum.type.bodyXSmall]. When [errorText] is non-null the field enters the
error state automatically. When [successText] is non-null (and [errorText]
is null) the field enters the success state with a green border and helper.

An optional character counter is shown in the support row when [maxLength]
is set to a positive value. Input exceeding [maxLength] is silently
truncated in [onValueChange].

@param value the current text field value
@param onValueChange callback invoked when the text changes
@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply to the outer column
@param label optional label displayed above / inside the field
@param placeholder optional placeholder shown when the field is empty
@param helperText optional assistive text shown below the field
@param errorText optional error text — when non-null the field shows
  error styling and this text replaces [helperText]
@param successText optional success text — when non-null (and no error)
  the field shows success styling with a green border
@param isError whether the field is in error state — defaults to
  `errorText != null`
@param isSuccess whether the field is in success state — defaults to
  `successText != null && !isError`
@param leading optional composable displayed at the start of the field
@param trailing optional composable displayed at the end of the field
@param enabled whether the field accepts input
@param readOnly whether the field is read-only (focusable but not editable)
@param singleLine whether the field is constrained to a single line
@param maxLines maximum number of visible lines
@param maxLength optional maximum character count — when positive, input is
  truncated and a counter is shown below the field
@param keyboardOptions software keyboard configuration
@param keyboardActions IME action callbacks
@param visualTransformation visual transformation applied to the input
@param shape the outline shape — defaults to 12 dp rounded corners

Aurum's icon primitive.

Renders an [ImageVector] at a configurable [size] (defaults to
[Aurum.iconSize.xl] = 24 dp, the canonical icon size in the Figma icon
library) with an optional [tint] colour filter.

This is a **scratch** component — built on [Image] from
`androidx.compose.foundation`, not on `material3.Icon`.

@param imageVector the icon to draw
@param contentDescription accessibility description — `null` means
  decorative (use sparingly)
@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply
@param size the icon size — defaults to [Aurum.iconSize.xl] (24 dp)
@param tint the colour filter applied to the icon. Defaults to
  [Aurum.colors.surface.iconDefaultNormal]

Aurum's numeric stepper — a compact container with decrease/value/increase
controls inside a single rounded container.

This is a **scratch** component — built on `androidx.compose.foundation`.

When [value] equals [minValue] (typically 0), the stepper shows an "Add"
button instead of the ±/value layout, matching the Figma "Initial State".

@param value the current numeric value
@param onValueChange called with the new value when the user taps ±
@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply
@param type visual style — [AurumStepperType.Neutral] or [Brand]
@param minValue minimum allowed value (inclusive) — defaults to 0
@param maxValue maximum allowed value (inclusive)
@param enabled whether the stepper is interactive

Aurum's root screen scaffold — the standard entry point for every
Aurum-powered screen.

Renders **edge-to-edge** by default. The top bar extends behind the
status bar; the bottom bar extends behind the navigation bar; the
content area is padded correctly via Scaffold's window insets.

## Usage

```kotlin
AurumScreen(
    topBar = {
        AurumTopAppBar(
            title = "Settings",
            onBack = { navController.popBackStack() },
        )
    },
    isLoading = viewModel.isLoading,
) { padding ->
    SettingsContent(Modifier.padding(padding))
}
```

@param modifier applied to the root container
@param topBar top bar slot — typically [AurumTopAppBar]. The top bar
  should apply `statusBarsPadding()` internally (AurumTopAppBar does
  this when `applyStatusBarInsets = true`)
@param bottomBar bottom bar slot — typically a CTA button row. Should
  apply `navigationBarsPadding()` internally if it sits at the screen
  bottom edge.
@param snackbarHostState the [SnackbarHostState] for showing snackbars.
  Call `snackbarHostState.showSnackbar(...)` from a coroutine.
@param isLoading when true, draws a full-screen scrim (including behind
  system bars) with a centered [AurumLoader]
@param containerColor the screen background colour — defaults to the
  Aurum page base (white in light mode)
@param contentWindowInsets the window insets that the content should
  respect. Defaults to [ScaffoldDefaults.contentWindowInsets] which
  handles the remaining system insets not consumed by top/bottom bars.
@param content the screen content lambda. Receives [PaddingValues] that
  account for the top bar, bottom bar, and system insets. Apply via
  `Modifier.padding(it)`.

components.signature:
@Composable
fun AurumSnackbar(
    snackbarData: SnackbarData,
    modifier: Modifier = Modifier,
)

components.kdoc:
Aurum's radio button — a single-choice selection control.

Maps to the Figma `radioButton` component (`5126:2507`) with three
variant axes (`isChecked`, `states`, `radioTypes`). Pass `label = null`
to render only the circle (Figma's `withoutLabel` variant).

Use [AurumRadioGroup] when you have a set of mutually-exclusive options;
this composable is the building block for one of those options.

@param selected whether this option is currently chosen
@param onClick called when the user taps the option, or `null` for
  read-only / non-interactive rendering (still respects [enabled])
@param modifier applied to the root container
@param label optional label text; `null` renders only the circle
@param subtext optional supporting text rendered below the label,
  indented to align with the label (32 dp from the radio side)
@param enabled whether the option is interactive — `false` fades the
  label/subtext to disabled colour and disables tap handling
@param error if `true`, the radio outline + dot are tinted with the
  feedback-negative colour. Use to signal validation failure
@param labelPosition where the label sits relative to the radio

Aurum's radio group — a vertical stack of mutually-exclusive options.

Maps to the Figma `RadioGroup` component (`5157:2034`) with two
variant axes (`Validation`, plus boolean `showLabel` / `showHelptext`).

Pass [errorText] to opt into the error variant: every option's circle
tints to feedback-negative and the helper line below switches from
the default disabled-grey to negative-normal.

@param options the choices, in display order
@param selected the currently-chosen value, or `null` if nothing is
  selected yet
@param onSelectionChange called with the new value when the user picks
  an option
@param modifier applied to the root column
@param label optional group label rendered above the options
@param helperText optional supporting text rendered below the options;
  suppressed when [errorText] is non-null
@param errorText error message — when non-null, switches the group
  into the validation-error visual; replaces [helperText]
@param enabled gates interaction for the entire group
@param labelPosition controls each option's label placement
  (see [AurumRadioLabelPosition])

Aurum's switch (toggle) component.

Allows users to toggle between two states (on/off) for immediate,
binary actions such as enabling or disabling a setting.

Wraps `material3.Switch` internally, overriding every visible style
parameter from Aurum tokens. Features consume this composable — never
`material3.Switch` directly.

@param checked whether the switch is currently in the "on" position
@param onCheckedChange called when the user toggles the switch, or `null`
  to make the switch read-only (still respects [enabled] for styling)
@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply
@param enabled whether the switch is interactive — defaults to `true`

Aurum's base container primitive.

A themed [Box] that applies background colour, shape clipping, optional
border, and optional elevation shadow. This is the building block for
cards, banners, and any other visually-distinct surface.

This is a **scratch** component — built on [Box] from
`androidx.compose.foundation`, not on `material3.Surface`.

@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply
@param color the surface fill colour — defaults to
  [Aurum.colors.surface.bgSurfaceLowContrast]
@param shape the clipping shape — defaults to [Aurum.shape.md]
@param borderColor the stroke colour — `null` means no border (default)
@param borderWidth the stroke width — defaults to [Aurum.borderWidth.sm]
@param elevation structured shadow recipe — `null` means flat (default)
@param content the composable content

Aurum's canonical text primitive.

Wraps [BasicText] (not `material3.Text`) and applies Aurum typography
tokens. If no [style] is provided, defaults to [Aurum.type.bodyMedium].

### Foreground resolution order
1. Explicit [color] parameter — overrides anything in [style], including a [Brush].
2. `style.brush` — gradient text passes through untouched (use `Aurum.type.foo.copy(brush = myBrush)`
   or construct a `TextStyle(brush = …, …)`).
3. `style.color` — honoured if set.
4. Aurum's default text colour ([Aurum.colors.surface.textDefaultNormal]).

This is a **scratch** component — built on `androidx.compose.foundation`
with zero `material3` imports.

@param text the text to display
@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply
@param style the [TextStyle] to use — prefer `Aurum.type.*` roles; may carry a [Brush]
@param color the text colour — prefer `Aurum.colors.*` tokens. When specified, overrides [style]'s foreground
  (brush or colour). Leave as [Color.Unspecified] to let the style decide.
@param textAlign optional text alignment override
@param maxLines maximum number of lines before truncation
@param overflow how visual overflow is handled
@param onTextLayout callback for text layout result
